Seit August 2022 diskutiert die Putin Regierung einen entsprechenden Entwurf, der auch Abtreibungen nach Vergewaltigung oder bei gesundheitlichen Problemen verbieten soll. Vor dem Hintergrund von Verarmung und Arbeitslosigkeit ist das ein zus\u00e4tzlicher Angriff auf Arbeiter:innen in Russland. Aber das Kanonenfutter f\u00fcr imperialistische Kriege w\u00e4chst eben nicht auf B\u00e4umen, sondern muss erpresst werden. Nicht ohne Grund sind momentan doppelt so viele Frauen bei den Antikriegs-Protesten und leider auch unter den politischen Gefangenen. Wir dokumentieren unter anderem Berichte von \"Feminist Against War\" \u00fcber das geplante Gesetz. "1468005593088598016", "name": "Biden and Putin speak again about the situation in Ukraine", "description": "Russian President Vladimir Putin and US President Joe Biden spoke again on the phone Thursday afternoon about Ukraine. Russia requested the call, according to The New York Times. Per the White House, Putin and Biden spoke for about 50 minutes. The leaders last call that was made known to the public was on December 7, when Russia said it would send ideas on the crisis to Washington "within a week," Reuters reported. The US Air Force flew two reconnaissance missions over eastern Ukraine this week, the first on December 27 just a few days after Russia said it would withdraw 10,000 troops from the shared border, CNN reported.

More on the leaders’ call:
- Ukraine has been a point of contention for the two countries since the annexation of Crimea in 2014, Al Jazeera reports

- Russia denied a new assault on Ukraine during the previous conversation and warned against any NATO military involvement, according to Reuters and Al Jazeera

- Biden warned Putin about possible sanctions against Russia in case of an escalation during the December 7 call, AFP reports"}}, {"domain": {"id": "29", "name": "Events [Entity Service]", "description": "Entity Service related Events domain"}, "entity": {"id": "1483255084750282753", "name": "Latest updates on the war in Ukraine", "description": "On February 24, Russia launched an invasion of Ukraine by land, air and sea after months of tensions between Moscow and Kyiv.
